name: ListMixin
comment:
Base implementation of a bot/dart-core.List class.

This class can be used as a mixin.

This implements all read operations using only the length and operator[] members. It implements write operations using those and length= and operator[]=

NOTICE: Forwarding just these four operations to a normal growable bot/dart-core.List (as created by new List()) will give very bad performance for add and addAll operations of ListBase. These operations are implemented by increasing the length of the list by one for each add operation, and repeatedly increasing the length of a growable list is not efficient. To avoid this, either override 'add' and 'addAll' to also forward directly to the growable list, or, if possible, use DelegatingList from "package:collection/wrappers.dart" instead.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment: Returns an Iterator that iterates over this Iterable object.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one element in this collection.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

last.name: last
last.comment:
Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

reversed.name: reversed
reversed.comment: Returns an dart-core.Iterable of the objects in this list in reverse order.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the bot/bot.ListMixin.elementAt.indexth element.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least bot/bot.ListMixin.elementAt.index elements in this.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function f to each element of this collection.

contains.name: contains
contains.comment: Returns true if the collection contains an element equal to bot/bot.ListMixin.contains.element.

every.name: every
every.comment: Returns true if every elements of this collection satisify the predicate bot/bot.ListMixin.every.test. Returns false otherwise.

any.name: any
any.comment: Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the predicate bot/bot.ListMixin.any.test. Returns false otherwise.

firstWhere.name: firstWhere
firstWhere.comment:
Returns the first element that satisfies the given predicate bot/bot.ListMixin.firstWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the bot/bot.ListMixin.firstWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when bot/bot.ListMixin.firstWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

lastWhere.name: lastWhere
lastWhere.comment:
Returns the last element that satisfies the given predicate bot/bot.ListMixin.lastWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the bot/bot.ListMixin.lastWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when bot/bot.ListMixin.lastWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

singleWhere.name: singleWhere
singleWhere.comment: Returns the single element that satisfies bot/bot.ListMixin.singleWhere.test. If no or more than one element match then a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

join.name: join
join.comment:
Converts each element to a dart-core.String and concatenates the strings.

Converts each element to a dart-core.String by calling bot/bot.ListMixin.toString on it. Then concatenates the strings, optionally separated by the bot/bot.ListMixin.join.separator string.

where.name: where
where.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable with all elements that satisfy the predicate bot/bot.ListMixin.where.test.

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function bot/bot.ListMixin.where.test will not be invoked. Iterating will not cache results, and thus iterating multiple times over the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function bot/bot.ListMixin.where.test multiple times on the same element.

map.name: map
map.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable where each element e of this is replaced by the result of f(e).

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function bot/bot.ListMixin.map.f will not be invoked. The transformed elements will not be cached. Iterating multiple times over the the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function bot/bot.ListMixin.map.f multiple times on the same element.

expand.name: expand
expand.comment:
Expands each element of this dart-core.Iterable into zero or more elements.

The resulting Iterable runs through the elements returned by bot/bot.ListMixin.expand.f for each element of this, in order.

The returned dart-core.Iterable is lazy, and calls bot/bot.ListMixin.expand.f for each element of this every time it's iterated.

reduce.name: reduce
reduce.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining elements of the collection using the provided function.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.reduce((value, element) => value + element);

fold.name: fold
fold.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining each element of the collection with an existing value using the provided function.

Use bot/bot.ListMixin.fold.initialValue as the initial value, and the function bot/bot.ListMixin.fold.combine to create a new value from the previous one and an element.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.fold(0, (prev, element) => prev + element);

skip.name: skip
skip.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips the first n elements.

If this has fewer than n elements, then the resulting Iterable is empty.

It is an error if n is negative.

skipWhile.name: skipWhile
skipWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips elements while bot/bot.ListMixin.skipWhile.test is satisfied.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable iterates over all elements of this.

As long as the iterator's elements satisfy bot/bot.ListMixin.skipWhile.test they are discarded. Once an element does not satisfy the bot/bot.ListMixin.skipWhile.test the iterator stops testing and uses every later element unconditionally. That is, the elements of the returned Iterable are the elements of this starting from the first element that does not satisfy bot/bot.ListMixin.skipWhile.test.

take.name: take
take.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable with at most n elements.

The returned dart-core.Iterable may contain fewer than n elements, if this contains fewer than n elements.

It is an error if n is negative.

takeWhile.name: takeWhile
takeWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that stops once bot/bot.ListMixin.takeWhile.test is not satisfied anymore.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable starts iterating over the elements of this.

When the iterator encounters an element e that does not satisfy bot/bot.ListMixin.takeWhile.test, it discards e and moves into the finished state. That is, it does not get or provide any more elements.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if bot/bot.ListMixin.toList.growable is false.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment: Creates a dart-core.Set containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

add.name: add
add.comment:
Adds value to the end of this list, extending the length by one.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if the list is fixed-length.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment:
Appends all objects of bot/bot.ListMixin.addAll.iterable to the end of this list.

Extends the length of the list by the number of objects in bot/bot.ListMixin.addAll.iterable. Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this list is fixed-length.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment:
Removes the first occurence of value from this list.

Returns true if value was in the list, false otherwise.

List<String> parts = ['head', 'shoulders', 'knees', 'toes'];
parts.remove('head'); // true
parts.join(', ');     // 'shoulders, knees, toes'

The method has no effect if value was not in the list.

// Note: 'head' has already been removed.
parts.remove('head'); // false
parts.join(', ');     // 'shoulders, knees, toes'

An dart-core.UnsupportedError occurs if the list is fixed-length.

removeWhere.name: removeWhere
removeWhere.comment:
Removes all objects from this list that satisfy bot/bot.ListMixin.removeWhere.test.

An object o satisfies bot/bot.ListMixin.removeWhere.test if test(o) is true.

List<String> numbers = ['one', 'two', 'three', 'four'];
numbers.removeWhere((item) => item.length == 3);
numbers.join(', '); // 'three, four'

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list.

retainWhere.name: retainWhere
retainWhere.comment:
Removes all objects from this list that fail to satisfy bot/bot.ListMixin.retainWhere.test.

An object o satisfies bot/bot.ListMixin.retainWhere.test if test(o) is true.

List<String> numbers = ['one', 'two', 'three', 'four'];
numbers.retainWhere((item) => item.length == 3);
numbers.join(', '); // 'one, two'

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list.

clear.name: clear
clear.comment:
Removes all objects from this list; the length of the list becomes zero.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError, and retains all objects, if this is a fixed-length list.

removeLast.name: removeLast
removeLast.comment:
Pops and returns the last object in this list.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list.

sort.name: sort
sort.comment:
Sorts this list according to the order specified by the bot/bot.ListMixin.sort.compare function.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.sort.compare function must act as a dart-core.Comparator.

List<String> numbers = ['one', 'two', 'three', 'four'];
// Sort from shortest to longest.
numbers.sort((x, y) => x.length.compareTo(y.length));
numbers.join(', '); // 'one, two, four, three'

The default List implementations use bot/dart-core.Comparable.compare if bot/bot.ListMixin.sort.compare is omitted.

List<int> nums = [13, 2, -11];
nums.sort();
     nums.join(', '); // '-11, 2, 13'

shuffle.name: shuffle
shuffle.comment: Shuffles the elements of this list randomly.

asMap.name: asMap
asMap.comment:
Returns an unmodifiable dart-core.Map view of this.

The map uses the indices of this list as keys and the corresponding objects as values. The Map.keys dart-core.Iterable iterates the indices of this list in numerical order.

List<String> words = ['fee', 'fi', 'fo', 'fum'];
Map<int, String> map = words.asMap();
map[0] + map[1];   // 'feefi';
map.keys.toList(); // [0, 1, 2, 3]

sublist.name: sublist
sublist.comment:
Returns a new list containing the objects from bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.end exclusive.

List<String> colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink'];
colors.sublist(1, 3); // ['green', 'blue']

If bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.end is omitted, the length of this is used.

colors.sublist(1);  // ['green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink']

An error occurs if bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.start is outside the range 0 .. length or if bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.end is outside the range start .. length.

getRange.name: getRange
getRange.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable that iterates over the objects in the range bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.end exclusive.

An error occurs if bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.end is before bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.start.

An error occurs if the bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.start and bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.end are not valid ranges at the time of the call to this method. The returned dart-core.Iterable behaves like skip(start).take(end - start). That is, it does not throw exceptions if this changes size.

List<String> colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink'];
Iterable<String> range = colors.getRange(1, 4);
range.join(', ');  // 'green, blue, orange'
colors.length = 3;
range.join(', ');  // 'green, blue'

removeRange.name: removeRange
removeRange.comment:
Removes the objects in the range bot/bot.ListMixin.removeRange.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.removeRange.end exclusive.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.removeRange.start and bot/bot.ListMixin.removeRange.end indices must be in the range 0 ≤ index ≤ length, and start ≤ end.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list. In that case the list is not modified.

fillRange.name: fillRange
fillRange.comment:
Sets the objects in the range bot/bot.ListMixin.fillRange.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.fillRange.end exclusive to the given fillValue.

An error occurs if bot/bot.ListMixin.fillRange.start..bot/bot.ListMixin.fillRange.end is not a valid range for this.

setRange.name: setRange
setRange.comment:
Copies the objects of bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.iterable, skipping bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.skipCount objects first, into the range bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.start, inclusive, to bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.end, exclusive, of the list.

List<int> list1 = [1, 2, 3, 4];
List<int> list2 = [5, 6, 7, 8, 9];
// Copies the 4th and 5th items in list2 as the 2nd and 3rd items
// of list1.
list1.setRange(1, 3, list2, 3);
list1.join(', '); // '1, 8, 9, 4'

The bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.start and bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.end indices must satisfy 0 ≤ start ≤ end ≤ length. If bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.start equals bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.end, this method has no effect.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.iterable must have enough objects to fill the range from start to end after skipping bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.skipCount objects.

If iterable is this list, the operation will copy the elements originally in the range from skipCount to skipCount + (end - start) to the range start to end, even if the two ranges overlap.

If iterable depends on this list in some other way, no guarantees are made.

replaceRange.name: replaceRange
replaceRange.comment:
Removes the objects in the range bot/bot.ListMixin.replaceRange.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.replaceRange.end exclusive and inserts the contents of replacement in its place.

List<int> list = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
list.replaceRange(1, 4, [6, 7]);
list.join(', '); // '1, 6, 7, 5'

An error occurs if bot/bot.ListMixin.replaceRange.start..bot/bot.ListMixin.replaceRange.end is not a valid range for this.

indexOf.name: indexOf
indexOf.comment:
Returns the first index of bot/bot.ListMixin.indexOf.element in this list.

Searches the list from index start to the end of the list. The first time an object o is encountered so that o == element, the index of o is returned.

List<String> notes = ['do', 're', 'mi', 're'];
notes.indexOf('re');    // 1
notes.indexOf('re', 2); // 3

Returns -1 if bot/bot.ListMixin.indexOf.element is not found.

notes.indexOf('fa');    // -1

lastIndexOf.name: lastIndexOf
lastIndexOf.comment: Returns the last index in the list a of the given bot/bot.ListMixin.lastIndexOf.element, starting the search at index bot/bot.ListMixin.lastIndexOf.startIndex to 0. Returns -1 if bot/bot.ListMixin.lastIndexOf.element is not found.

insert.name: insert
insert.comment:
Inserts the object at position bot/bot.ListMixin.insert.index in this list.

This increases the length of the list by one and shifts all objects at or after the index towards the end of the list.

An error occurs if the bot/bot.ListMixin.insert.index is less than 0 or greater than length. An dart-core.UnsupportedError occurs if the list is fixed-length.

removeAt.name: removeAt
removeAt.comment:
Removes the object at position bot/bot.ListMixin.removeAt.index from this list.

This method reduces the length of this by one and moves all later objects down by one position.

Returns the removed object.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.removeAt.index must be in the range 0 ≤ index < length.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list. In that case the list is not modified.

insertAll.name: insertAll
insertAll.comment:
Inserts all objects of bot/bot.ListMixin.insertAll.iterable at position bot/bot.ListMixin.insertAll.index in this list.

This increases the length of the list by the length of bot/bot.ListMixin.insertAll.iterable and shifts all later objects towards the end of the list.

An error occurs if the bot/bot.ListMixin.insertAll.index is less than 0 or greater than length. An dart-core.UnsupportedError occurs if the list is fixed-length.

setAll.name: setAll
setAll.comment:
Overwrites objects of this with the objects of bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.iterable, starting at position bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.index in this list.

List<String> list = ['a', 'b', 'c'];
list.setAll(1, ['bee', 'sea']);
list.join(', '); // 'a, bee, sea'

This operation does not increase the length of this.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.index must be non-negative and no greater than length.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.iterable must not have more elements than what can fit from bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.index to length.

If iterable is based on this list, its values may change /during/ the setAll operation.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

length=.name: length=
length=.comment:
Changes the length of this list.

If bot/bot.ListMixin.length=.newLength is greater than the current length, entries are initialized to null.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if the list is fixed-length.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides bot/bot.ListMixin.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of objects in this list.

The valid indices for a list are 0 through length - 1.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment: Returns an Iterator that iterates over this Iterable object.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one element in this collection.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

last.name: last
last.comment:
Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

reversed.name: reversed
reversed.comment: Returns an dart-core.Iterable of the objects in this list in reverse order.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and bot/bot.ListMixin.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the bot/bot.ListMixin.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

[].comment: Returns the object at the given bot/bot.ListMixin.[].index in the list or throws a dart-core.RangeError if bot/bot.ListMixin.[].index is out of bounds.

[]=.comment: Sets the value at the given bot/bot.ListMixin.[]=.index in the list to bot/bot.ListMixin.[]=.value or throws a dart-core.RangeError if bot/bot.ListMixin.[]=.index is out of bounds.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
bot/bot.ListMixin.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to bot/bot.ListMixin.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If bot/bot.ListMixin.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of bot/bot.ListMixin.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

map.name: map
map.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable where each element e of this is replaced by the result of f(e).

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function bot/bot.ListMixin.map.f will not be invoked. The transformed elements will not be cached. Iterating multiple times over the the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function bot/bot.ListMixin.map.f multiple times on the same element.

contains.comment: Returns true if the collection contains an element equal to bot/bot.ListMixin.contains.element.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function bot/bot.ListMixin.forEach.f to each element of this collection.

reduce.name: reduce
reduce.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining elements of the collection using the provided function.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.reduce((value, element) => value + element);

fold.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining each element of the collection with an existing value using the provided function.

Use bot/bot.ListMixin.fold.initialValue as the initial value, and the function bot/bot.ListMixin.fold.combine to create a new value from the previous one and an element.

Converts each element to a dart-core.String by calling bot/bot.ListMixin.toString on it. Then concatenates the strings, optionally separated by the bot/bot.ListMixin.join.separator string.

any.comment: Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the predicate bot/bot.ListMixin.any.test. Returns false otherwise.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if bot/bot.ListMixin.toList.growable is false.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment: Creates a dart-core.Set containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

take.name: take
take.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable with at most bot/bot.ListMixin.take.n elements.

The returned dart-core.Iterable may contain fewer than bot/bot.ListMixin.take.n elements, if this contains fewer than bot/bot.ListMixin.take.n elements.

It is an error if bot/bot.ListMixin.take.n is negative.

takeWhile.name: takeWhile
takeWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that stops once bot/bot.ListMixin.takeWhile.test is not satisfied anymore.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable starts iterating over the elements of this.

When the iterator encounters an element e that does not satisfy bot/bot.ListMixin.takeWhile.test, it discards e and moves into the finished state. That is, it does not get or provide any more elements.

skip.name: skip
skip.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips the first bot/bot.ListMixin.skip.n elements.

If this has fewer than bot/bot.ListMixin.skip.n elements, then the resulting Iterable is empty.

It is an error if bot/bot.ListMixin.skip.n is negative.

skipWhile.name: skipWhile

firstWhere.name: firstWhere
firstWhere.comment:

lastWhere.name: lastWhere
lastWhere.comment:
Returns the last element that satisfies the given predicate bot/bot.ListMixin.lastWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the bot/bot.ListMixin.lastWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when bot/bot.ListMixin.lastWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

singleWhere.name: singleWhere
singleWhere.comment: Returns the single element that satisfies bot/bot.ListMixin.singleWhere.test. If no or more than one element match then a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the bot/bot.ListMixin.elementAt.indexth element.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than bot/bot.ListMixin.length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least bot/bot.ListMixin.elementAt.index elements in this.

add.name: add
add.comment:

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if the list is fixed-length.

Extends the length of the list by the number of objects in bot/bot.ListMixin.addAll.iterable. Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this list is fixed-length.

sort.name: sort
sort.comment:
Sorts this list according to the order specified by the bot/bot.ListMixin.sort.compare function.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.sort.compare function must act as a dart-core.Comparator.

List<String> numbers = ['one', 'two', 'three', 'four'];
// Sort from shortest to longest.
numbers.sort((x, y) => x.length.compareTo(y.length));
numbers.join(', '); // 'one, two, four, three'

The default List implementations use bot/dart-core.Comparable.compare if bot/bot.ListMixin.sort.compare is omitted.

List<int> nums = [13, 2, -11];
nums.sort();
     nums.join(', '); // '-11, 2, 13'

shuffle.name: shuffle
shuffle.comment: Shuffles the elements of this list randomly.

indexOf.name: indexOf
indexOf.comment:
Returns the first index of bot/bot.ListMixin.indexOf.element in this list.

Searches the list from index bot/bot.ListMixin.indexOf.start to the end of the list. The first time an object o is encountered so that o == element, the index of o is returned.

List<String> notes = ['do', 're', 'mi', 're'];
notes.indexOf('re');    // 1
notes.indexOf('re', 2); // 3

Returns -1 if bot/bot.ListMixin.indexOf.element is not found.

notes.indexOf('fa');    // -1

lastIndexOf.name: lastIndexOf
lastIndexOf.comment:
Returns the last index of bot/bot.ListMixin.lastIndexOf.element in this list.

Searches the list backwards from index bot/bot.ListMixin.lastIndexOf.start to 0.

The first time an object o is encountered so that o == element, the index of o is returned.

List<String> notes = ['do', 're', 'mi', 're'];
notes.lastIndexOf('re', 2); // 1

If bot/bot.ListMixin.lastIndexOf.start is not provided, this method searches from the end of the list./Returns

notes.lastIndexOf('re');  // 3

Returns -1 if bot/bot.ListMixin.lastIndexOf.element is not found.

notes.lastIndexOf('fa');  // -1

clear.name: clear
clear.comment:
Removes all objects from this list; the length of the list becomes zero.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError, and retains all objects, if this is a fixed-length list.

insert.name: insert
insert.comment:
Inserts the object at position bot/bot.ListMixin.insert.index in this list.

This increases the length of the list by one and shifts all objects at or after the index towards the end of the list.

An error occurs if the bot/bot.ListMixin.insert.index is less than 0 or greater than length. An dart-core.UnsupportedError occurs if the list is fixed-length.

insertAll.name: insertAll
insertAll.comment:
Inserts all objects of bot/bot.ListMixin.insertAll.iterable at position bot/bot.ListMixin.insertAll.index in this list.

This increases the length of the list by the length of bot/bot.ListMixin.insertAll.iterable and shifts all later objects towards the end of the list.

An error occurs if the bot/bot.ListMixin.insertAll.index is less than 0 or greater than length. An dart-core.UnsupportedError occurs if the list is fixed-length.

setAll.name: setAll
setAll.comment:
Overwrites objects of this with the objects of bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.iterable, starting at position bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.index in this list.

List<String> list = ['a', 'b', 'c'];
list.setAll(1, ['bee', 'sea']);
list.join(', '); // 'a, bee, sea'

This operation does not increase the length of this.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.index must be non-negative and no greater than bot/bot.ListMixin.length.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.iterable must not have more elements than what can fit from bot/bot.ListMixin.setAll.index to bot/bot.ListMixin.length.

If iterable is based on this list, its values may change /during/ the setAll operation.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment:
Removes the first occurence of bot/bot.ListMixin.remove.value from this list.

Returns true if bot/bot.ListMixin.remove.value was in the list, false otherwise.

List<String> parts = ['head', 'shoulders', 'knees', 'toes'];
parts.remove('head'); // true
parts.join(', ');     // 'shoulders, knees, toes'

The method has no effect if bot/bot.ListMixin.remove.value was not in the list.

// Note: 'head' has already been removed.
parts.remove('head'); // false
parts.join(', ');     // 'shoulders, knees, toes'

An dart-core.UnsupportedError occurs if the list is fixed-length.

removeAt.name: removeAt
removeAt.comment:
Removes the object at position bot/bot.ListMixin.removeAt.index from this list.

This method reduces the length of this by one and moves all later objects down by one position.

Returns the removed object.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.removeAt.index must be in the range 0 ≤ index < length.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list. In that case the list is not modified.

removeLast.name: removeLast
removeLast.comment:
Pops and returns the last object in this list.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list.

removeWhere.name: removeWhere
removeWhere.comment:
Removes all objects from this list that satisfy bot/bot.ListMixin.removeWhere.test.

An object o satisfies bot/bot.ListMixin.removeWhere.test if test(o) is true.

List<String> numbers = ['one', 'two', 'three', 'four'];
numbers.removeWhere((item) => item.length == 3);
numbers.join(', '); // 'three, four'

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list.

retainWhere.name: retainWhere
retainWhere.comment:
Removes all objects from this list that fail to satisfy bot/bot.ListMixin.retainWhere.test.

An object o satisfies bot/bot.ListMixin.retainWhere.test if test(o) is true.

List<String> numbers = ['one', 'two', 'three', 'four'];
numbers.retainWhere((item) => item.length == 3);
numbers.join(', '); // 'one, two'

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list.

sublist.name: sublist
sublist.comment:
Returns a new list containing the objects from bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.end exclusive.

List<String> colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink'];
colors.sublist(1, 3); // ['green', 'blue']

If bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.end is omitted, the bot/bot.ListMixin.length of this is used.

colors.sublist(1);  // ['green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink']

An error occurs if bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.start is outside the range 0 .. length or if bot/bot.ListMixin.sublist.end is outside the range start .. length.

getRange.name: getRange
getRange.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable that iterates over the objects in the range bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.end exclusive.

An error occurs if bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.end is before bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.start.

An error occurs if the bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.start and bot/bot.ListMixin.getRange.end are not valid ranges at the time of the call to this method. The returned dart-core.Iterable behaves like skip(start).take(end - start). That is, it does not throw exceptions if this changes size.

List<String> colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink'];
Iterable<String> range = colors.getRange(1, 4);
range.join(', ');  // 'green, blue, orange'
colors.length = 3;
range.join(', ');  // 'green, blue'

setRange.name: setRange
setRange.comment:
Copies the objects of bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.iterable, skipping bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.skipCount objects first, into the range bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.start, inclusive, to bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.end, exclusive, of the list.

List<int> list1 = [1, 2, 3, 4];
List<int> list2 = [5, 6, 7, 8, 9];
// Copies the 4th and 5th items in list2 as the 2nd and 3rd items
// of list1.
list1.setRange(1, 3, list2, 3);
list1.join(', '); // '1, 8, 9, 4'

The bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.start and bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.end indices must satisfy 0 ≤ start ≤ end ≤ length. If bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.start equals bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.end, this method has no effect.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.iterable must have enough objects to fill the range from start to end after skipping bot/bot.ListMixin.setRange.skipCount objects.

If iterable is this list, the operation will copy the elements originally in the range from skipCount to skipCount + (end - start) to the range start to end, even if the two ranges overlap.

If iterable depends on this list in some other way, no guarantees are made.

removeRange.name: removeRange
removeRange.comment:
Removes the objects in the range bot/bot.ListMixin.removeRange.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.removeRange.end exclusive.

The bot/bot.ListMixin.removeRange.start and bot/bot.ListMixin.removeRange.end indices must be in the range 0 ≤ index ≤ length, and start ≤ end.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if this is a fixed-length list. In that case the list is not modified.

fillRange.name: fillRange
fillRange.comment:
Sets the objects in the range bot/bot.ListMixin.fillRange.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.fillRange.end exclusive to the given bot/bot.ListMixin.fillRange.fillValue.

An error occurs if bot/bot.ListMixin.fillRange.start..bot/bot.ListMixin.fillRange.end is not a valid range for this.

replaceRange.name: replaceRange
replaceRange.comment:
Removes the objects in the range bot/bot.ListMixin.replaceRange.start inclusive to bot/bot.ListMixin.replaceRange.end exclusive and inserts the contents of bot/bot.ListMixin.replaceRange.replacement in its place.

List<int> list = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
list.replaceRange(1, 4, [6, 7]);
list.join(', '); // '1, 6, 7, 5'

An error occurs if bot/bot.ListMixin.replaceRange.start..bot/bot.ListMixin.replaceRange.end is not a valid range for this.

asMap.name: asMap
asMap.comment:
Returns an unmodifiable dart-core.Map view of this.

The map uses the indices of this list as keys and the corresponding objects as values. The Map.keys dart-core.Iterable iterates the indices of this list in numerical order.

List<String> words = ['fee', 'fi', 'fo', 'fum'];
Map<int, String> map = words.asMap();
map[0] + map[1];   // 'feefi';
map.keys.toList(); // [0, 1, 2, 3]
